== Wizard
/* Wizard, Mage, Sorcerer, Witch */
Magic is incredible and everyone else wishes they got the letter to go and study it. 
You're a wizard, hurray, so that is exactly what you do. 
Play this class to access a wide range of spells. 

You have Advantage on tests: (Pick 3)
- Of knowledge. 
- Of perceptiveness. 
- 
- To make creative use of a spell. 

*Spellbook.*
Grab a stack of index cards, sticky notes or a small notebook to be your _spellbook_. 
In the fiction, your spellbook is an actual book, scroll, or tablet you can wield in one hand. 
When you wield a spellbook you can: 
 - Mark Stress to cast a spell you know, not included among your special actions. 
 - _Mark_ and _clear_ things in it. 

When rules allow you to *mark* something in the spellbook, write it down. 
When you *clear*, rip the sticky note, erase or cross it out in the notebook --- get rid of it. 

Arcane Bolt
Mark Stress, spend 2 actions. 
2d6i and mark the target's species in your spellbook (human, bear, griffin, etc). Clear it to gain Advantage on a test related to a creature of the same kind. 

ILLUSIONIST
Mirrored Trio: Mark Stress to gain 3 Images. Mark an Image to clear a damage die showing an odd result. 

ABJUROR
Magnetic field. (Passive) Whenever a damage die is rolled on you due to a metal weapon, arrowhead or similar, you can decide to reroll it once. 

Lorebook. 
(+1d12) Recall lore. 
(Ability) Attack. Roll 1d4 damage on a foe close to you. 
Mark stress to reroll one damage die included in a spell. 

Implement of flame. "Burn something down: 2"
Spend 1 to add 1 Fire to a foe when you attack. 

Implement of ice. "Freeze something over: 2"
Spend 1 to add 1 Cold to a foe when you attack. 


Elementalist. 
Channel the elements. 
Add Fire or Cold to a foe. 
Shift one ambient Fire, Cold to a foe. 
Roll 1d4 damage for each of them. 
Bonus: Also turn one into another other. 

Fire mage spells. 
Spark. Roll 1d4 damage, add a Fire threat. 
Bonfire. Manifest a roaring fire, but mark stress absent suitable fuel. 
Clear an ambient Cold or Dark, and add ambient Fire. 
Roll 1d4 damage per Fire to a close target. 
Fireball (far). Roll up to 8d6 damage, split between your target and others close to it. No more than 3d6 per target. Add 2 ambient Fire. 
